    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the carrot has slightly softened, reduce the heat to medium-high</p><p>Add your <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> to the pan with <strong>half </strong>your<strong> sliced spring onion </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Add your<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Be careful – the ginger and garlic will sizzle from the heat of the oil!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
